                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18020918-90-off479 t18020918-90-crimeloc482"></join>, the prisoner was <rs id="t18020918-90-deflabel483" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18020918-90-defend664 t18020918-90-deflabel483"></join> in the house where we lodged; I missed the linen off a chest, and saw a part of the cap on her head, I knew it by the lace; she confessed it, and we found a calico gown behind her bed, and a shirt on her; I found some keys on her, which opened my drawers. (The property was produted and identified.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. The shirt and cap lay on my bed, and being short of linen, I took the shirt till such time as I had washed my own; the woman saw the cap on my head, it belonged to her; I gave it her, and they took me up for stealing them, which I had not; as for the keys, I know nothing of them. <rs id="t18020918-90-verdict484" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18020918-90-verdict484" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 17.</p>
